The Gifting Tree of Black Rock City;

You are coming home, it’s time to roam;

Through the lovely, Black Rock City;

Come look, come see, our gifting tree;

Impart, enjoy our art, be apart, and open your hearts;

Black Rock heaven gifting will be 24-seven;

Don’t be squirrely, here it’s never too late or too early;

Home, free from danger, leave some presents for a stranger;

Happily help yourself to a gift for you, because we love you too.

Come anytime and bring some things while remembering;

Anything that does not go, to and fro, into the trash we must throw;

A note of thanks for thoughtful presents yet, may the truest gift be your presence.

Tree- By Michael Pierce.

Poem- Valerie Wagner.

A special thank you Carl Blume, Monera, Curtis Sill, EJ The DJ. Clarice Tara for your help with some of the painting on the project. I get by with a little help from my friends. -Beatles
